## Implementation Details

### 1. Footer Centering Fix (src/components/Footer.tsx)

**Problem:** Footer pill appeared visually off-center despite correct CSS.

**Root Cause:** Asymmetric content (save status on right side) created visual imbalance.

**Solution:**
- Changed `transform -translate-x-1/2` class to inline `style={{ transform: 'translateX(-50%)' }}` for CSS specificity
- Added `justify-center` to inner flex container
- Added `whitespace-nowrap` to prevent text wrapping
- Improved hover states for empty days

**Lines Changed:** 38-83 (45 lines)

**Code:**
```tsx
<motion.footer
  className="fixed bottom-4 left-1/2 z-30 pointer-events-none"
  style={{ transform: 'translateX(-50%)' }}
>
  <div className="flex items-center justify-center gap-4...">
```

### 2. Calendar Double-Click Interaction (src/components/TimeEntryCalendar.tsx)

**Problem:** No way to interact with calendar days directly (had to use "New Event" button).

**Solution:**
- Added `onDoubleClick={() => handleDayClick(dateStr)}` to day cells
- Added `cursor-pointer` class for visual feedback
- Added `title="Double-click to add event"` tooltip
- Enhanced hover states for empty days

**Lines Changed:** 370-382 (12 lines)

**Code:**
```tsx
<div
  key={dateStr}
  onDoubleClick={() => handleDayClick(dateStr)}
  className="...cursor-pointer..."
  title="Double-click to add event"
>
```

